				\begin{document}$\vert B \vert $\end{document} complicates the analysis of instrument zeroes as described by Vasquez et al. (2020). Since there is relatively less Range-3 (least sensitive) than Range-1 (higher sensitivity) data and the resolution is reduced, we perform our alignment analyses using Range-1 data only. Fig. 3
Magnetic field intensity as measured by RBSP-A on October 16, 2012. Values above ∼5×103\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
