				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$f_{pe}$\end{document} because it could be that the continuum radiation is cutoff at a remote location and the density at the spacecraft is actually somewhat lower. Fig. 16
[From Kurth et al. 2015]: Examples of Van Allen Probe A Waves High Frequency Receiver spectrograms illustrating some of the varieties of forms the spectra take on depending on the level of activity of the magnetosphere. The inference of electron densities from the frequency of the upper hybrid resonance band relies on the proper identification of fuh\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
